<item>
            <title>[AMQ-3748] ActiveMQEndpointWorker$1: Run method is synchronized</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3748</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As posted in this mail &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; by Ed Keen there is a issue in the ActiveMQEndpointWorker.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I checked the spec the JBoss guys mentioned and in section 10.3.2 it is clearly stated:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Both the run and release methods in the Work implementation may contain&lt;br/&gt;
synchronization blocks but they must not be declared as synchronized methods.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Removing the &quot;synchronized&quot; worked for some people trying this. But I think it was added intentionally, so somebody should check an appropriate alternative.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug prevents ActiveMQ from being deployed on JBoss AS 7.1&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/activemq-users/201202.mbox/%3CCAC=rkz2XZmJo3D03kHG6nfz0c800-Mh=9JH6qb=zeGQyU=MNXQ@mail.gmail.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/activemq-users/201202.mbox/%3CCAC=rkz2XZmJo3D03kHG6nfz0c800-Mh=9JH6qb=zeGQyU=MNXQ@mail.gmail.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;a href=&quot;http://download.oracle.com/otn-pub/jcp/connector_architecture-1.6-fr-oth-JSpec/connector-1_6-final-spec.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://download.oracle.com/otn-pub/jcp/connector_architecture-1.6-fr-oth-JSpec/connector-1_6-final-spec.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
